Deep Research Engine (DRE)
1. Purpose of This Document
This document defines the authoritative data model for the Deep Research Engine (DRE).
It specifies:
  canonical tables / collections
  primary keys and relationships
  immutability and versioning rules
  replay and audit guarantees
This model is optimized for evidence provenance, long-horizon knowledge retention, and governed promotion.
2. Data Modeling Principles
 Evidence Is Immutable — captured facts are never edited or deleted
 Versioned Knowledge Artifacts — hypotheses, narratives, and assumptions evolve via versions
 Append-Only Decisions — interpretation changes are recorded, not overwritten
 Graph-First Relationships — entities and claims are linkable and time-scoped
 Cross-Engine Stability — IDs remain stable across PIE, SIM, DAT, GGP
